0because%20their%20stars%20boil%20the%20planets'%20outer%20layers%20away%20%E2%80%94%20evaporating%20mass%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWASP-69b%20is%20much%20bigger%20than%20a%20sub-Neptune%2C%20but%20it's%20demonstrating%20the%20exact%20boiling%20behavior%20that%20scientists%20suspect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it's%20so%20large%2C%20it%20takes%20much%20longer%20to%20lose%20its%20atmosphere%2C%20giving%20scientists%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20study%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudying%20this%20Jupiter-sized%20world%20and%20its%20long%20comet-like%20tail%20can%20teach%20us%20more%20about%20the%20physics%20of%20space%2C%20including%20how%20planets%20and%20their%20host%20stars%20evolve%20together%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20WASP-69b%20system%20is%20a%20gem%20because%20we%20have%20a%20rare%20opportunity%20to%20study%20atmospheric%20mass-loss%20in%20real%20time%20and%20understand%20the%20critical%20physics%20that%20shape%20thousands%20of%20other%20planets%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.ucla.edu%2Freleases%2Fa-jupiter-sized-planet-was-hiding-a-350-000-mile-long-tail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EErik%20Petigura%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20study%20co-author%20and%20UCLA%20professor%20of%20physics%20and%20astronomy%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjupiter-sized-planet-boiled-alive-creating-comet-like-tail-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704857101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659de8d96979d7371821df0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjupiter-sized-planet-boiled-alive-creating-comet-like-tail-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20exoplanet%20WASP-69b%20is%20orbiting%20its%20host%20star%20so%20closely%20that%20the%20intense%20radiation%20is%20literally%20boiling%20the%20planet's%20atmosphere%20into%20space.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22