0fraud-trial%20closings%2C%20but%20only%20with%20a%20judge's%20approval.%3Cp%3EInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20Trump's%20attorney%2C%20Alina%20Habba%2C%20nor%20a%20spokesperson%20immediately%20commented%20on%20his%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo-called%20%26quot%3Bhybrid%20representation%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20uncommon%20in%20criminal%20trials%2C%20but%20it's%20rare%20in%20civil%20cases%2C%20said%20veteran%20New%20York%20City%20attorney%20Ron%20Kuby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJudge%20Engoron%20may%20well%20simply%20say%2C%20'Go%20ahead.%20You%20cannot%20possibly%20do%20more%20damage%20to%20yourself%20than%20you've%20already%20done%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kuby%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20would%20be%20little%20downside%20for%20the%20judge%20in%20approving%20Trump's%20request%2C%20he%20added%2C%20noting%2C%20%26quot%3BHe'd%20never%20be%20reversed%20on%20appeal%20over%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20delivering%20closing%20arguments%2C%20Trump%20would%20be%20bound%20by%20the%20same%20rules%20as%20an%20attorney%20would%2C%20Kuby%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20can%20only%20argue%20what%20the%20evidence%20has%20shown%2C%20what%20the%20evidence%20has%20not%20shown%2C%20and%20what%20reasonable%20inferences%20can%20be%20drawn%20from%20the%20evidence%2C%26quot%3B%20Kuby%20said%20of%20pro-se%20defendants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20defendant%20can't%20just%20sit%20up%20there%20and%20shriek%20until%20the%20judge%20hits%20them%20with%20a%20rolled-up%20newspaper%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20quipped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20defendant%20chiming%20in%20on%20his%20lawyer's%20closing%20statements%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20unusual%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20career%20New%20York%20City%20trial%20attorney%20Michael%20Farkas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20not%20prohibited%20by%20the%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20agreed%20Farkas%2C%20a%20retired%20military%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20Judge%20Engoron%20would%20be%20hard-pressed%20to