er%20his%20duties%20on%20January%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-prostate-cancer-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProstate%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20second%20to%20lung%20cancer%20as%20the%20most%20deadly%20form%20of%20cancer%20facing%20American%20men%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cancer.org%2Fcancer%2Ftypes%2Fprostate-cancer%2Fabout%2Fkey-statistics.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Cancer%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%201%20in%2043%20men%20dying%20from%20the%20disease.%20However%2C%20when%20caught%20early%2C%20prostate%20cancer%20is%20treatable%20and%20has%20a%2099%25%20survival%20rate%20over%20five%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pcf.org%2Fabout-prostate-cancer%2Fwhat-is-prostate-cancer%2Fprostate-cancer-survival-rates%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProstate%20Cancer%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalter%20Reed%20officials%20indicated%20in%20their%20statement%20Austin's%20cancer%20was%20detected%20early%20and%20his%20prognosis%20is%20%26quot%3Bexcellent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20have%20argued%20the%20lack%20of%20clarity%20surrounding%20Austin's%20health%20status%2C%20particularly%20as%20the%20country%20is%20navigating%20wars%20fought%20by%20US-backed%20allies%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-gaza-hamas-war-benefit-putin-russia-ukraine-invasion-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboth%20Israel%20and%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rattles%20the%20faith%20of%20the%20American%20people%20and%20calls%20into%20question%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20Defense%20Department%20as%20well%20as%20the%20competence%20of%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20hope%20people%20will%20understand%20is%20that%20the%20national%20security%20decision%20making%20process%20does%20not%20require%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%20fact%20should%20not%20require%20%E2%80%94%20cabinet-level%20officials%20being%20the%20sole%20people%20in%20the%20room%20making%20decisions%20on%20any%20given%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20said%20in%20the%20Tuesday%20press%20conference%20in%20response%20to%20pointed%20questioning%20regarding%20the%20transparency%20and%20credibility%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20Pentagon%20has%20been%20very%20honest%20with%20the%20challenge%20to%20credibility%20by%20what%20has%20transpired%20here%2C%20and%20how%20hard%20it%20was%20for%20them%20to%20be%20fully%20transparent%20with%20the%20American%20people.%20I%20think%20we%20all%20recognize%20that%20this%20didn't%20unfold%20the%20way%20it%20should%20have%20on%20so%20many%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20the%20notification%20process%20of%20the%20chain%20of%20command%2C%20but%20the%20transparency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20directed%20Business%20Insider%20to%20Ryder's%20Tuesday%20press%20conference%20but%20declined%20to%20answer%20questions%20about%20why%20Austin%20chose%20not%20to%20inform%20the%20White%20House%20of%20his%20diagnosis%20or%20how%20the%20DOD%20plans%20to%20address%20concerns%20over%20transparency%20caused%20by%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20recognize%20that%20we%20have%20to%20do%20a%20better%20job%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20timeliness%20and%20transparency%20when%20it%20comes%20to%2C%20especially%2C%20the%20Secretary's%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryder%20said%20in%20the%20Tuesday%20press%20conference.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we're%20committed%20to%20making%20sure%20that%20we%20don't%20do%20this%20again%2C%20and%20that%20we%20do%20a%20better%20job%20next%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%2