al%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-chitradurga-india-police_6416128.jpg%3F20240109141829%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsuchana-seth-arrest-dead-body-of-four-year-old-son-found-in-indian-ai-start-up-bosss-luggage-13044749%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20chief%20executive%20of%20an%20AI%20start-up%20has%20been%20arrested%20after%20her%20four-year-old%20son's%20body%20was%20found%20in%20her%20luggage%2C%20police%20have%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A48%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsuchana-seth-arrest-dead-body-of-four-year-old-son-found-in-indian-ai-start-up-bosss-luggage-13044749%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsuchana-seth-arrest-dead-body-of-four-year-old-son-found-in-indian-ai-start-up-bosss-luggage-13044749%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsuchana-seth-arrest-dead-body-of-four-year-old-son-found-in-indian-ai-start-up-bosss-luggage-13044749%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vijayakanth's%20Political%20Journey%20Was%20a%20Blend%20of%20Aspiration%2C%20Courage%2C%20Mistakes%20and%20Harsh%20Realities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09182944%2FVijayakanth.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fvijayakanth-no-more%5C%22%3Epassing%20of%20Vijayakanth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20eminent%20Tamil%20film%20star-turned-politician%2C%20marks%20the%20end%20of%20a%20significant%20albeit%20overlooked%20chapter%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20political%20narrative.%20His%20transition%20from%20the%20movie%20industry%20to%20the%20political%20arena%20was%20not%20just%20a%20career%20shift%2C%20but%20a%20transformative%20journey%20that%20redefined%20the%20contours%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20political%20and%20social%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20film%20career%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20his%20political%20journey.%20As%20the%20elected%20president%20of%20the%20South%20Indian%20Artistes%E2%80%99%20Association%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Nadigar%20Sangam%2C%20he%20demonstrated%20his%20ability%20to%20lead%20and%20mediate%20in%20an%20industry%20rife%20with%20socio-economic%20and%20political%20divisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20work%20in%20the%20Nadigar%20Sangam%20in%20the%20late%201990s%20and%20early%202000s%20provides%20a%20valuable%20lens%20to%20understand%20the%20interplay%20of%20the%20Dravidian-Tamil%20ethos%20among%20the%20Tamil%20diaspora%20across%20the%20world.%20His%20popularity%20in%20cinema%20and%20his%20philanthropy%20did%20not%20just%20win%20him%20fans%2C%20but%20built%20an%20organisational%20base%20that%20later%20morphed%20into%20a%20political%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20media%20profile%20and%20portrayal%20of%20heroic%20characters%20resonated%20with%20the%20public%20at%20the%20time%2C%20crafting%20an%20image%20of%20a%20benevolent%20and%20approachable%20leader.%20Crucially%2C%20the%20financial%20success%20of%20his%20film%20career%20provided%20the%20resources%20necessary%20to%20fuel%20his%20political%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKaruppu%3C%2Fem%3E%20MGR%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20politics%20of%20subversion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20film%20persona%2C%20reminiscent%20of%20M.G.%20Ramachandran%20(MGR)%E2%80%99s%20style%2C%20helped%20him%20appeal%20to%20a%20wide%20electorate.%20His%20leadership%20in%20the%202006%20assembly%20elections%20and%20the%202009%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20established%20his%20Desiya%20Murpokku%20Dravida%20Kazhagam%20(DMDK)%20party%20as%20a%20notable%20force%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20politics%20was%20marked%20by%20an%20astute%20use%20of%20populism.%20Though%20he%20was%20popularly%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKaruppu%20%3C%2Fem%3EMGR%E2%80%99%20(dark-skinned%20MGR)%20due%20to%20the%20similarities%20in%20their%20persona%20and%20of%20their%20screen%20titles%2C%20Vijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20style%20of%20politics%20was%20in%20effect%20a%20subversion%20of%20MGR%E2%80%99s%20style%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-trojan-horse-left-winger-vagueness-at-the-heart-of-kamal-haasans-politics%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98BJP%20Trojan%20Horse%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Left%20Winger%E2%80%99%3A%20Vagueness%20at%20the%20Heart%20of%20Kamal%20Haasan%E2%80%99s%20Politics%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20observed%20by%20Dr%20Andrew%20Wyatt%2C%20Vijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20political%20strategy%20mirrored%20the%20%E2%80%98protectionist%E2%80%99%20populism%20of%20MGR%2C%20i.e.%20the%20amalgamation%20of%20diverse%20social%20groups%20rather%20than%20catering%20to%20specific%20caste%2C%20regional%20or%20sub-regional%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20unlike%20MGR%2C%20Vijayakanth%20neither%20sought%20nor%20secured%20the%20definitive%20support%20of%20numerically%20dominant%20caste%20groups.%20Instead%2C%20he%20built%20a%20broad%20coalition%20of%20support%20by%20voicing%20his%20opposition%20to%20caste-based%20parties%20and%20focusing%20on%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20marginalised.%20Such%20an%20approach%20sought%20to%20unsettle%20the%20sub-regional%20geographic%20dominance%20exerted%20by%20a%20few%20numerically%20dominant%20caste%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20outreach%20to%20women%20and%20the%20symbolic%20use%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Emurasu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(drum)%2C%20an%20emblem%20of%20the%20marginalised%20(Dalits)%2C%20in%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20imagery%2C%20demonstrated%20an%20astute%20understanding%20of%20social%20dynamics%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20of%20the%20Dravidian-Tamil%20ethos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20set%20him%20up%20to%20transcend%20traditional%20caste%20and%20class%20barriers%20in%20gaining%20support%20from%20diverse%20groups%20across%20the%20state%2C%20bringing%20his%20style%20of%20politics%20closer%20to%20the%20DMK%20and%20Karunanidhi%20in%20particular.%20This%20explains%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20considerable%20vote%20shares%20in%20the%202006%20and%202009%20elections%2C%20which%20translated%20into%20seats%20when%20in%20alliance%20with%20a%20Dravidian%20major%2C%20the%20AIADMK%2C%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDMDK%E2%80%99s%20short-lived%20success%20and%20the%20Dravidian%20majors%E2%80%99%20resilience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Wyatt%20noted%20that%20the%20DMDK%20grappled%20with%20maintaining%20institutional%20pluralism.%20The%20centralisation%20of%20power%20around%20Vijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20persona%20and%20the%20uncertain%20tolerance%20for%20diverse%20opinions%20within%20the%20party%20raised%20questions%20about%20its%20long-term%20institutional%20health.%20A%20case%20in%20point%20is%20his%20refusal%20to%20cater%20to%20his%20party-wide%20request%20to%20form%20an%20alliance%20with%20the%20DMK%20ahead%20of%20the%202016%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20while%20his%20outreach%20strategy%20was%20congruent%20with%20Karunanidhi%E2%80%99s%2C%20he%20could%20not%20be%20the%20conciliator-in-chief%20within%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20his%20stardom%20and%20hold%20over%20the%20party%20and%20its%20members%20were%20not%20comparable%20to%20that%20of%20MGR.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20he%20could%20not%20prevent%20defections%20and%20could%20not%20find%20replacements%20for%20such%20defectors%20in%20the%20corresponding%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frajinikanth-tamil-nadu-politics-vijayakanth-dmdk%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Vijayakanth%20in%20Tamil%20Politics%2C%20Rajinikanth%20Has%20a%20Lesson%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20deteriorating%20health%20and%20the%20emergence%20of%20his%20family%20members%20at%20the%20helm%20who%20could%20not%20fill%20his%20shoes%2C%20and%20more%20importantly%2C%20tomfoolery%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20alliance%20decisions%2C%20enfeebled%20the%20party%20and%20its%20electoral%20prospects%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20effect%2C%20the%20DMDK%20lost%20ideological%20coherence%20and%20a%20stable%20connect%20with%20the%20people.%20The%20Dravidian%20majors%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20after%20a%20few%20initial%20setbacks%2C%20were%20able%20to%20regain%20their%20electoral%20dominance%20and%2C%20in%20the%20process%2C%20saw%20more%20members%20of%20the%20DMDK%20join%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20despite%20effectuating%20substantive%20impact%2C%20he%20did%20not%20draw%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20political%20discourse%20and%20opinion%20makers%20akin%20to%20that%20of%20his%20fellow%20actors%20like%20Rajinikanth%20or%20Kamal%20Haasan%2C%20who%20drew%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20even%20over%20non-committal%20signalling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20be%20attributed%20to%20Vijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20last%20few%20movies%20that%20neither%20succeeded%20financially%20nor%20resonated%20with%20audiences%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20a%20weaker%20connect%20with%20his%20fans%20since%20he%20started%20his%20political%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20failed%20to%20proactively%20create%20a%20communication%20ecosystem%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20public%20and%20the%20discourse-makers%3B%20worse%2C%20when%20he%20got%20his%20opportunities%2C%20he%20damaged%20his%20reputation%20by%20losing%20his%20composure%20on%20camera%20and%20in%20public%20many%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdieu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20political%20endeavours%2C%20while%20short-lived%2C%20created%20significant%20ripples%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20politics.%20His%20efforts%20illuminate%20the%20electoral%20arena%E2%80%99s%20receptiveness%20to%20charismatic%20leaders%20while%20also%20underscoring%20the%20importance%20of%20building%20robust%20party%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20retrospect%2C%20Vijayakanth%E2%80%99s%20political%20journey%20was%20a%20blend%20of%20aspiration%2C%20courage%2C%20mistakes%20and%20the%20harsh%20realities%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20political%20arena.%20As%20we%20bid%20farewell%20to%20Vijayakanth%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20acknowledge%20his%20unique%20contribution%20to%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20political%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20story%20is%20not%20just%20about%20the%20transient%20impact%20of%20a%20celebrity%20in%20politics%2C%20but%20also%20about%20the%20broader%20dynamics%20of%20power%2C%20culture%20and%20populism%20in%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20politically%20vibrant%20states.%20His%20legacy%2C%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20potential%20and%20limitations%20of%20star%20power%20in%20politics%2C%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20subject%20of%20interest%20and%20analysis%20for%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fvignesh-karthik-kr%5C%22%3EVignesh%20Karthik%20K.R.%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20Postdoctoral%20Research%20Fellow%20of%20Indian%20and%20Indonesian%20Politics%20at%20the%20Royal%20Netherlands%20Institute%20of%20Southeast%20Asian%20and%20Caribbean%20Studies.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704806146000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09182944%2FVijayakanth.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fvijayakanth-an-apparent-enigma-in-tamil-nadus-politics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20recently%20passed%20film%20star-turned-politician's%20efforts%20illuminate%20the%20electoral%20arena's%20receptiveness%20to%20charismatic%20leaders%20while%20also%20underscoring%20the%20importance%20of%20building%20robust%20party%20structures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fvijayakanth-an-apparent-enigma-in-tamil-nadus-politics%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20the%20Defence%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Visit%20to%20the%20UK%20Could%20Be%20Pivotal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09174855%2FScreenshot-2024-01-09-at-5.48.17.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20visit%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20to%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20from%20January%208-10%2C%20the%20first%20Indian%20Defence%20Ministerial%20visit%20to%20the%20UK%20in%2022%20years%2C%20marks%20a%20significant%20improvement%20in%20bilateral%20ties%20and%20the%20building%20of%20trust%20despite%20differences%20over%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20defence%20technological%20and%20industrial%20partnerships%2C%20a%20key%20objective%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20boost%20self-reliance%20in%20arms%20production%2C%20remains%20challenging%20with%20the%20reluctance%20of%20UK%20defence%20industry%20to%20engage%20boldly%20with%20India%2C%20unlike%20their%20counterparts%20in%20the%20US%20and%20France.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%202002%2C%20George%20Fernandes%2C%20the%20defence%20minister%20of%20an%20earlier%20BJP-led%20government%2C%20visited%20London%20amidst%20an%20India-Pakistan%20military%20crisis.%20Several%20junior%20defence%20ministers%20have%20visited%20since%20then%2C%20largely%20for%20defence%20and%20air%20shows.%20A%20planned%20visit%20to%20the%20UK%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022%20by%20current%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20was%20abruptly%20called%20off%20by%20India%20for%20%E2%80%98protocol%E2%80%99%20reasons.%20But%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20the%20Indian%20side%20felt%20they%20could%20not%20usefully%20engage%20with%20then%20UK%20Defence%20Secretary%20Ben%20Wallace%2C%20who%20perceived%20India%20as%20%E2%80%98not%20on%20side%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%20Since%20the%20appointment%20of%20his%20successor%20Grant%20Shapps%2C%20an%20inaugural%20meeting%20of%20the%20%E2%80%982%2B2%E2%80%99%20foreign%20and%20defence%20dialogue%20at%20Director%20General-level%2C%20took%20place%20in%20October%202023%20and%20the%20Defence%20Consultative%20Group%20meeting%20at%20Permanent%20Secretary-level%20was%20held%20in%20November%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Defence%20and%20Security%E2%80%99%20are%20one%20of%20five%20%E2%80%98pillars%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20India-UK%202030%20Roadmap%2C%20launched%20by%20prime%20ministers%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Boris%20Johnson%20in%20May%202021%2C%20setting%20out%20a%20unique%20ten-year%20bilateral%20plan%20for%20prioritization%20and%20raising%20ties%20to%20a%20Comprehensive%20Strategic%20Partnership.%20During%20the%20meeting%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%20in%20September%202023%2C%20prime%20ministers%20Modi%20and%20Sunak%20agreed%20to%20build%20%E2%80%98a%20modern%20partnership%20in%20cutting-edge%20defence%20technology%2C%20trade%20and%20innovation%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UK%20government%20supports%20India%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20develop%20its%20defence%20industry%2C%20which%20would%20reduce%20its%20dependence%20on%20Russian%20military%20equipment.%20In%20April%202022%2C%20it%20issued%20an%20India-specific%20open%20general-export%20license%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20given%20to%20an%20Indo-Pacific%20country%20%E2%80%93%20to%20permit%20exports%20of%20certain%20military%20and%20dual-use%20goods%20and%20technology.%20In%20September%202023%2C%20the%20UK%20launched%20a%20new%20organisation%20headed%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20called%20Defence%20Partnership%20India%20to%20build%20bilateral%20defence%20ties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20no%20significant%20India-UK%20collaboration%20regarding%20defence%20capabilities%20has%20occurred%20as%20yet.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reason%20for%20this%20is%20that%20its%20implementation%20depends%20on%20industry%20not%20government%2C%20marked%20by%20a%20notable%20lack%20of%20coordination%20and%20cooperation%20between%20the%20two.%20It%20is%20also%20affected%20by%20what%20an%20IISS%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EStrategic%20Comment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20November%202023%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98three-I%E2%80%99%20challenge%20for%20UK%20companies%20in%20relation%20to%20India.%20These%20pertain%20to%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20i)%20foreign%20investment%20%E2%80%93%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20Indian%20procurement%20category%20of%20majority%20foreign%20ownership%20for%20the%20most%20lucrative%20projects%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eii)%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20%E2%80%93%20the%20requirement%20for%20intellectual%20property%20for%20such%20projects%20to%20be%20Indian%20owned%20and%20controlled%3B%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eiii)%20indigenous-content%20requirements%20%E2%80%93%20a%20minimum%20level%20of%2050%25%20or%20more%20to%20be%20domestically-sourced%20for%20the%20parts%20and%20materials%20used%20in%20weapons%20or%20equipment.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20also%20concern%20that%20sensitive%20technologies%20could%20be%20diverted%20from%20India%20to%20Russia%3B%20which%20the%20Indian%20government%20stoutly%20challenges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-uk-trade-talks-not-stalled-indian-government-sources-deny-uk-newspaper-report%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98India-UK%20Trade%20Talks%20Not%20Stalled%E2%80%99%3A%20Indian%20Government%20Sources%20Deny%20UK%20Newspaper%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20defence%20minister%E2%80%99s%20visit%20could%20prove%20pivotal%20by%20progressing%20significant%20collaborative%20projects%20at%20a%20political%20level.%20The%20most%20important%20are%20the%20co-development%20and%20co-creation%20of%20gas-turbine%20propulsion%20technology%20by%20Rolls-Royce%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20(DRDO)%20for%20the%20next-generation%20of%20Indian%20fighter-aircraft%20engines%2C%20where%20India%20will%20own%20the%20project%E2%80%99s%20most%20sensitive%20intellectual%20property%20as%20well%20as%20export-approval%20authority%3B%20the%20recent%20partnership%20for%20naval%20electric%20propulsion%20between%20the%20Indian%20government%20and%20GE%20(Naval)%2C%20UK%20as%20well%20as%20Rolls-Royce%3B%20and%20the%20procurement%20of%20ground-based%20air%20defence%20systems%20from%20MBDA%20(UK).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Ministerial%20visit%20takes%20place%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20DRDO%20has%20shut%20down%20its%20office%20in%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20in%20London%20and%20re-located%20its%20single%20official%20representative%20to%20France%3B%20and%20the%20Indian%20defence%20ministry%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20rationalisation%20process%2C%20has%20reduced%20its%20military%20representation%20in%20London%20from%20three%20one-star%20officers%20to%20a%20single%20officer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditional%20challenges%20could%20include%20the%20emergence%20of%20firm%20evidence%20on%20allegations%20of%20official%20Indian%20involvement%20in%20targeted%20assassinations%2Fassassination%20attempts%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%3B%20as%20well%20as%20a%20rise%20in%20Sikh%20separatist%20(Khalistani)%20extremism%20in%20the%20UK%20amidst%20upcoming%20general%20elections%20in%20India%20(in%20May-June%202023)%20and%20the%20UK%20(in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year)%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20finalised%20bilateral%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERahul%20Roy-Chaudhury%20is%20Senior%20Fellow%20for%20South%20Asia%2C%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%20(IISS)%2C%20London.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704804320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09174855%2FScreenshot-2024-01-09-at-5.48.17.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwhy-the-defence-ministers-visit-to-the-uk-could-be-pivotal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22No%20significant%20India-UK%20collaboration%20regarding%20defence%20capabilities%20has%20occurred%20as%20yet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwhy-the-defence-ministers-visit-to-the-uk-could-be-pivotal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Andhra%20Pradesh%20Is%20a%20Political%20Pesarattu%20in%20the%20Making%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09174323%2FFBFtwuhVIAAyQIL.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20significance%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20in%20the%20complex%20matrix%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20democracy%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20understated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20played%20a%20decisive%20role%20in%20ousting%20the%20incumbent%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee-led%20BJP%20government%20in%202004.%20The%20Congress%2C%20then%20led%20by%20its%20stalwart%20leader%20Y.S.%20Rajasekhara%20Reddy%2C%20won%2029%20out%20of%20the%2042%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituencies%20of%20the%20state%2C%20and%20helped%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20edge%20past%20the%20BJP%20that%20was%20riding%20high%20on%20its%20raucous%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20Shining%E2%80%9D%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20Reddy%20steered%20his%20party%20to%20another%20remarkable%20victory%20by%20increasing%20the%20tally%20to%2034%2C%20again%20piloting%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20return%20to%20power%20at%20the%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty%20years%20later%2C%20much%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20dynamics%20has%20changed.%20For%20one%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20now%20has%20only%2025%20seats.%20The%20remaining%2017%20have%20gone%20to%20Telangana%20that%20was%20formed%20in%202014.%20The%20bifurcation%20of%20the%20state%20sounded%20the%20death%20knell%20of%20Congress%20hopes%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20even%20as%20it%20clawed%20back%20into%20power%20in%20Telangana%20in%202023%20after%20almost%20a%20decade%20of%20struggle.%20Almost%20the%20entire%20Congress%20unit%20shifted%20to%20the%20YSR%20Congress%20formed%20by%20Rajasekhara%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20son%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%2C%20who%20registered%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20victories%20in%20the%202019%20assembly%20elections%20against%20its%20principal%20rival%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20led%20by%20N.%20Chandrababu%20Naidu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20all%20the%20political%20churn%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20too%2C%20has%20remained%20unsuccessful%20in%20making%20inroads%20in%20the%20state.%20It%20has%20attempted%20to%20poach%20influential%20leaders%20from%20both%20the%20TDP%20and%20YSR%20Congress%2C%20pressed%20both%20the%20regional%20parties%20to%20toe%20its%20political%20line%20in%20the%20Parliament%20by%20keeping%20federal%20funds%20tightly%20under%20its%20control%2C%20and%20kept%20the%20Sword%20of%20Damocles%20hanging%20over%20both%20Jagan%20and%20Naidu%E2%80%99s%20heads%20through%20central%20investigation%20agencies.%20The%20carrot%20and%20stick%20approach%20adopted%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20BJP%20towards%20both%20the%20YSR%20Congress%20and%20TDP%2C%20however%2C%20has%20alienated%20the%20saffron%20party%20further%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20regional%20parties%20have%20taken%20a%20special%20dislike%20towards%20the%20BJP%20for%20its%20alleged%20blackmailing%20tactics%20and%20are%20willing%20to%20work%20with%20the%20Centre%20only%20for%20convenience%20instead%20of%20any%20true%20ideological%20reasons.%20The%20tricky%2C%20multi-layered%20politics%20that%20is%20currently%20unfolding%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20set%20to%20witness%20another%20round%20of%20simultaneous%20assembly%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20in%202024%2C%20is%20a%20case%20in%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Finterview-telugu-desam-party-nara-lokesh-jaganmohan%5C%22%3ETDP%20scion%20Nara%20Lokesh%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20that%20it%20has%20adopted%20an%20%E2%80%9Cequidistant%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20towards%20both%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP.%20Given%20that%20the%20TDP%20has%20historically%20been%20an%20anti-Congress%20platform%20and%20has%20been%20a%20part%20of%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20earlier%2C%20the%20new%20posturing%20is%20significant.%20Lokesh%20denied%20all%20reports%20that%20spoke%20about%20a%20possible%20TDP-BJP%20alliance%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20The%20party%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20is%20focussed%20on%20Jagan%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cautocratic%E2%80%9D%20regime%20that%2C%20according%20to%20Lokesh%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20an%20all-round%20disenfranchisement%20of%20democratic%20institutions%20in%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Panchayats%20to%20Vidhan%20Sabha.%20%E2%80%9COver-centralisation%E2%80%9D%20of%20governance%20during%20Jagan%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20Lokesh%20said%2C%20has%20led%20to%20corrupt%20and%20crony%20practices%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20party%20has%20also%20attacked%20Jagan%20for%20supporting%20many%20of%20the%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20bills%20in%20the%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETDP%E2%80%99s%20line%20of%20canvassing%20bears%20stark%20resemblance%20to%20the%20larger%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20against%20the%20Modi%20government.%20Most%20TDP%20leaders%20will%20privately%20tell%20you%20that%20the%20Jagan%20government%20is%20no%20different%20from%20the%20Modi%20government%20in%20the%20way%20it%20functions.%20Yet%2C%20TDP%20has%20not%20taken%20an%20open%20stance%20against%20the%20Centre%2C%20something%20that%20it%20did%20when%20N.%20Chandrababu%20Naidu%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20in%202018.%20It%20has%20allied%20with%20the%20Pawan%20Kalyan-led%20Jana%20Sena%2C%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20NDA%20in%20Telangana.%20Lokesh%20said%20that%20Jana%20Sena%20is%20a%20BJP%20ally%20only%20in%20Telangana%20but%20not%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20as%20he%20asserted%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cequidistant%E2%80%9D%20policy%20from%20both%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObservers%20in%20the%20state%20believe%20that%20any%20hope%20of%20an%20alliance%20between%20the%20TDP%20and%20the%20BJP%20were%20dashed%20by%20Jagan%20when%20his%20government%20arrested%20Naidu%20in%20a%20corruption%20case%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20saffron%20party%20to%20officially%20ally%20with%20the%20TDP.%20Given%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20anti-corruption%20rhetoric%2C%20Jagan%20practically%20checkmated%20both%20its%20principal%20rival%20TDP%20and%20the%20BJP%2C%20while%20sending%20a%20strong%20message%20to%20the%20Centre%20to%20let%20both%20the%20regional%20parties%20fight%20it%20out%20on%20their%20own%20in%20the%20upcoming%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJagan%2C%20however%2C%20is%20beset%20with%20his%20own%20problems.%20In%202019%2C%20he%20consolidated%20a%20majority%20of%20minority%20and%20Dalit%20votes%20in%20his%20favour.%20He%20has%20pursued%20a%20strong%20secular%20political%20line%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20while%20also%20delivering%20a%20slew%20of%20welfare%20measures%20to%20the%20poor.%20However%2C%20his%20support%20to%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20bills%20in%20Parliament%20may%20have%20also%20driven%20away%20a%20substantial%20section%20of%20his%20supporters%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20have%20been%20traditional%20Congress%20workers%2C%20from%20his%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%202024%20elections%2C%20he%20is%20struggling%20to%20keep%20his%20house%20in%20order.%20His%20sister%20YS%20Sharmila%2C%20who%20was%20sidelined%20in%20the%20party%2C%20recently%20joined%20the%20Congress%20and%20is%20touted%20to%20play%20a%20prominent%20role%20in%20Andhra%20politics%20in%20the%20days%20to%20come.%20Her%20last-minute%20decision%20to%20withdraw%20from%20the%20recent%20electoral%20race%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20victory%20in%20Telangana%20assembly%20elections.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20many%20of%20his%20MLAs%20are%20facing%20strong%20anti-incumbency%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20forcing%20Jagan%20to%20announce%20many%20new%20faces%20as%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20candidates.%20Moreover%2C%20his%20welfarist%20measures%20for%20the%20poor%20have%20alienated%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20middle%20class%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20his%20own%20popularity%20among%20the%20poor%20counts%20in%20the%20upcoming%20assembly%20elections%20in%20the%20face%20of%20such%20hurdles%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%2C%20as%20a%20class%20divide%20among%20the%20voters%20is%20increasingly%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%20palpable.%20Naidu%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20shown%20his%20ability%20to%20resuscitate%20after%20a%20string%20of%20failures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telugu%20parties%20remain%20malleable%20enough%20to%20move%20towards%20both%20UPA%20and%20NDA.%20Ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20tried%20hard%20to%20gain%20a%20foothold%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20resigned%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20has%20no%20hope%20of%20any%20electoral%20gain%20in%20the%20coastal%20state.%20It%20will%20mostly%20rely%20on%20its%20alleged%20pressure%20tactics%20to%20sway%20one%20of%20the%20regional%20parties%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20complicated%20post-poll%20scenario.%20Regional%20concerns%20and%20state%E2%80%99s%20autonomy%20will%20dictate%20political%20decisions%20made%20by%20both%20the%20TDP%20and%20YSR%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%20laid%20the%20foundation%20stone%20for%20its%20revival%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20by%20inducting%20Y.S.%20Sharmila.%20However%2C%20its%20way%20forward%20currently%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20long-winding%20and%20laborious%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704802517000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09174323%2FFBFtwuhVIAAyQIL.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fandhra-pradesh-in-flux-political-pesarattu-in-the-making%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amidst%20all%20the%20political%20churn%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20too%2C%20has%20remained%20unsuccessful%20in%20making%20inroads%20in%20the%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fandhra-pradesh-in-flux-political-pesarattu-in-the-making%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Earth%20shattered%20global%20heat%20record%20in%202023%20and%20it's%20flirting%20with%20warming%20limit%2C%20European%20agency%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704802112000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106670396%2Cimgsize-695075.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fhome%2Fenvironment%2Fweather%2F2023-hottest-year-on-record-as-earth-nears-critical-1-5c-limit-monitor%2Farticleshow%2F106670294.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20bo