upported%20by%20various%20groups%2C%20including%20Kuki%20Inpi%20Tengnoupal%20and%20HTC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20minister%20Biren%20Singh%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20the%20possible%20involvement%20of%20mercenaries%20from%20Myanmar%20in%20the%20recent%20attacks.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20doubts%20about%20the%20involvement%20of%20foreign%20mercenaries%20from%20the%20Myanmar%20side%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20He%20has%20raised%20similar%20arguments%20since%20the%20violence%20began%20on%20May%203%2C%20but%20critics%20have%20argued%20that%20it%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20evade%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20responsibility%20in%20failing%20to%20control%20the%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManipur%20has%20been%20grappling%20with%20ethnic%20violence%20since%20early%20May%20when%20clashes%20between%20the%20Meiteis%20and%20the%20tribal%20Kuki%20community%20broke%20out%2C%20resulting%20in%20nearly%20200%20casualties.%20The%20ethnic%20tension%20has%20deepened%20to%20a%20point%20that%20community-based%20armed%20village%20defence%20volunteers%20have%20come%20up%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704781050000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31100356%2FGCm-A9Pa4AAS-Sn.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fgunfight-continues-in-manipurs-moreh-over-200-villagers-forced-to-leave-their-homes%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Moreh%2C%20situated%20along%20the%20Myanmar%20border%2C%20had%20been%20on%20high%20alert%20following%20a%20series%20of%20attacks%20by%20militants%20on%20security%20forces%2C%20particularly%20targeting%20Manipur%20police%20commandos.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fgunfight-continues-in-manipurs-moreh-over-200-villagers-forced-to-leave-their-homes%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bhutan's%20Elections%20Are%20a%20Time%20to%20Recognise%20the%20Glory%20of%20Democracy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09104658%2F38483611462_4a890e6997_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Bhutan%20enters%20the%20last%20stage%20of%20its%20fourth%20national%20elections%2C%20many%20observers%20%E2%80%93%20including%20many%20Bhutanese%20%E2%80%93%20are%20talking%20about%20the%20unhappiness%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9CHappy%20Kingdom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20is%20true%20that%20there%20is%20no%20shortage%20of%20problems.%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20economy%20is%20in%20a%20mess%2C%20its%20long-standing%20employment%20crisis%20is%20fuelling%20a%20migration%20of%20young%20out%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20it%20is%20facing%20its%20most%20challenging%20external%20security%20environment%20in%20decades.%20But%20what%20is%20harder%20to%20see%2C%20is%20how%20successfully%20Bhutan%20has%20transitioned%20from%20an%20almost%20absolute%20monarchy%20into%20a%20vibrant%20and%20maturing%20democracy%20in%20the%20short%20time%20since%20its%20first%20national%20elections%20in%202008.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scale%20of%20the%20transition%20is%20hard%20to%20grasp%20easily%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20it%20is%20often%20overlooked.%20It%20was%20the%20third%20king%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20the%20dynamic%20Jigme%20Dorji%20Wangchuck%2C%20who%20established%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20National%20Assembly%20in%201953%20%E2%80%93%20barely%20a%20year%20into%20his%20reign%20from%201952%20to%201972.%20During%20this%20time%2C%20he%20transformed%20the%20country%3B%20freeing%20serfs%2C%20ushering%20in%20land%20reforms%2C%20and%20establishing%20the%20infrastructure%20that%20would%20transform%20the%20country%20from%20a%20subsistence%20economy%20to%20now%20having%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20per%20capita%20GDPs%20in%20the%20region.%20Nonetheless%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20gave%20the%20National%20Assembly%20the%20power%20to%20remove%20the%20king%20(a%20clause%20his%20son%2C%20the%20fourth%20king%2C%20would%20modify)%2C%20the%20country%20was%20an%20almost%20total%20monarchy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESalman%20Haidar%2C%20who%20served%20as%20our%20Ambassador%20to%20Bhutan%20from%201980%20to%201983%2C%20said%20that%20the%20best%20understanding%20of%20the%20Bhutanese%20monarchy%20at%20that%20time%20was%20to%20view%20it%20as%20equivalent%20to%20the%20monarchies%20in%20Shakespearean%20plays.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20in%20%5Bthe%20play%5D%20Henry%20IV%2C%20for%20the%20fourth%20king%20%5BJigme%20Singye%20Wangchuck%5D%20the%20king%20and%20the%20country%20were%20one.%20Bhutan%20was%20what%20he%20was.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20governance%20philosophy%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20the%20pledge%20that%20most%20Bhutanese%20civil%20servants%20make%2C%20is%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETsa%20Wa%20Sum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20loosely%20to%20the%20king%2C%20country%2C%20and%20people%2C%20as%20one%20unit.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%202013%2C%202014%2C%202015%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmo.gov.bt%2F%3Fpage_id%3D7055%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estate%20of%20the%20nation%20addresses%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20second%20elected%20Bhutanese%20prime%20minister%2C%20Tshering%20Topgay%2C%20were%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20State%20of%20Tsa%20Wa%20Sum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20deep%20association%20with%20the%20king%20and%20governance%20is%20what%20made%20the%20democratic%20transition%20so%20hard.%20Many%20Bhutanese%20felt%20the%20king%20was%20abandoning%20them%2C%20and%20they%20trusted%20him%20more%20than%20their%20own%20choice%20of%20people%20to%20govern%20them.%20Since%20education%20standards%2C%20health%2C%20life%20expectancy%2C%20wages%2C%20and%20well-being%20had%20all%20increased%20during%20the%20fourth%20king%E2%80%99s%20long%20reign%20(1972-2008)%20before%20his%20abdication%20in%20favour%20of%20his%20son%2C%20the%20current%20Druk%20Gyalpo%2C%20or%20king%2C%20Jigme%20Khesar%20Wangchuck%2C%20this%20was%20understandable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20mock%20elections%2C%20held%20in%202007%2C%20to%20teach%20the%20people%20how%20to%20vote%2C%20there%20were%20four%20%E2%80%98stand-in%E2%80%99%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20Yellow%20for%20tradition%2C%20Green%20for%20sustainable%20ecology%2C%20Red%20for%20industrial%20development%2C%20and%20Blue%20for%20a%20fair%20and%20corruption-free%20society.%20Yellow%2C%20though%2C%20is%20also%20associated%20with%20the%20monarchy%20and%20monastic%20orders%2C%20and%20it%20was%20no%20surprise%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2FidUSDEL19868%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E46%20out%20of%2047%20constituencies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20voted%20for%20Yellow.%20Covering%20the%20first%20real%20elections%20in%202008%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20differentiate%20between%20the%20pledges%20of%20the%20Druk%20Phuensum%20Tshogpa%20(which%20won%20the%20elections)%20and%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Democratic%20Party.%20A%20Bhutanese%20friend%20explained%20it%20in%20the%20following%20way%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20PDP%20is%20royalist%20and%20traditionalist%2C%20and%20DPT%20is%20more%20royalist%20and%20more%20traditionalist.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20such%20things%20are%20easy%20to%20joke%20about%2C%20they%20were%20the%20principal%20hurdle%20for%20the%20democratic%20transition.%20Democracy%20is%20about%20the%20peaceful%20transition%20of%20power%2C%20based%20on%20the%20differing%20pathways%20that%20political%20parties%20offer.%20But%2C%20desperately%20afraid%20of%20criticising%20the%20royalist%20past%2C%20Bhutanese%20political%20parties%20did%20the%20opposite.%20Bhutan%20doubled%20down%20on%20what%20it%20had%20done%20in%20the%20past.%20Hydropower%2C%20which%20was%20the%20principal%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20country%2C%20was%20set%20to%20be%20expanded.%20High-end%20tourism%2C%20the%20second%20largest%20source%20of%20revenue%20and%20the%20highest%20employment%20sector%2C%20was%20expanded%20as%20well.%20The%20one%20piece%20of%20innovation%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcs.org%2Fcomm_select.php%3FarticleNo%3D3963%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eminor%20outreach%20to%20China%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20first%20elected%20prime%20minister%2C%20Jigme%20Yoser%20Thinley%20%E2%80%93%20received%20such%20a%20strong%20backlash%20from%20India%2C%20that%20it%20is%20often%20seen%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailyo.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbhutan-nepal-china-india-wen-jiabao-jigme-yoeser-thinley-lpg-narendra-modi-7331%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrongly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20as%20the%20main%20reason%20for%20him%20to%20lose%20the%202013%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20overcautious%20approach%20to%20the%20past%20has%20been%20costly%20for%20Bhutan.%20In%202008%2C%20Bhutan%20pledged%20to%20increase%20its%20hydropower%20capacity%20from%201%2C480%20MW%20to%2010%2C000%20MW%20in%202020.%20It%20has%20managed%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fenergy%2Fbhutan-failed-hydropower-goal-and-geopolitics-of-energy%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eonly%20increase%20it%20to%202%2C326%20MW%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20huge%20projects%20are%20over%20budget%20and%20long%20delayed%2C%20adding%20to%20huge%20economic%20strain%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20finances%2C%20since%20they%20are%20principally%20funded%20by%20loans%20from%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20had%20a%20crippling%20impact%20on%20the%20tourism%20industry%2C%20and%20a%20ham-handed%20response%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhutantoday.bt%2Fexceeds-expectations-with-over-16000-visitors-since-reopening-despite-sdf-increase%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreasing%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Fee%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202022%20across%20all%20sectors%20did%20little%20to%20help%2C%20leading%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ttgasia.com%2F2023%2F11%2F23%2Fbhutan-tourism-looking-bright-with-reduction-of-sustainable-development-fees%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E50%25%20reduction%20of%20the%20SDF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20The%20fixation%20on%20hydropower%20(with%20few%20jobs)%20and%20an%20unclear%20vision%20on%20tourism%2C%20has%20led%20to%20an%20exacerbation%20of%20a%20youth%20unemployment%20problem%2C%20which%20a%20worrying%20trend%20of%20Bhutanese%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fbhutans-jobs-woes-drive-an-exodus-australia-2023-07-28%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emigrating%20to%20places%20like%20Australia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%2C%20on%20its%20border%2C%20with%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20principal%20security%20guarantor%20%E2%80%93%20unable%20or%20unwilling%20to%20manage%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fon-the-india-china-border-disengagement-is-not-resolution%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoutcome%20of%20the%20Galwan%20imbroglio%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Bhutan%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chathamhouse.org%2Fpublications%2Fthe-world-today%2F2023-12%2Fchina-takes-more-land-bhutan-expected-border-deal%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreasingly%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20accommodate%20Chinese%20claims%20on%20an%20unresolved%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-china-doklam-real-problem-bhutan%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Real%20Problem%20Lies%20in%20its%20Bhutan%20Policy%2C%20Not%20the%20Border%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20it%20would%20seem%20to%20be%20that%20democracy%20has%20not%20brought%20much%20happiness%20to%20the%20Kingdom%20which%20coined%20the%20term%20Gross%20National%20Happiness%20(GNH).%20In%20fact%2C%20given%20that%20dissatisfaction%20is%20what%20leads%20people%20to%20vote%20out%20governments%2C%20the%20Bhutanese%20have%20well%20demonstrated%20their%20unhappiness.%20Bhutan%20has%20voted%20out%20every%20party%20that%20has%20won%20power%20%E2%80%93%20the%20DPT%20in%202013%2C%20the%20PDP%20in%202018%2C%20and%20the%20last%20governing%20party%2C%20and%20the%20Druk%20Nyamrup%20Tshogpa%20(DNT)%20which%20governed%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%20has%20already%20been%20knocked%20out%20in%20the%20first%20round%20of%20the%20current%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGNH%20as%20a%20governing%20philosophy%2C%20though%2C%20has%20never%20been%20about%20this%20type%20of%20happiness.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalip%20Mehta%2C%20who%20served%20as%20ambassador%20to%20Bhutan%20from%201995%20to%201998%2C%20was%20posted%20as%20junior%20diplomat%20in%20the%20country%20during%20the%201970s%2C%20when%20the%20fourth%20king%E2%80%99s%20term%20became%20well%20known.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20Mehta%20told%20me%2C%20the%20king%20was%20returning%20from%20an%20international%20conference%2C%20and%20was%20confronted%20by%20a%20pushy%20Indian%20journalist%20who%20asked%20him%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20rule%20a%20country%20with%20the%20lowest%20Gross%20National%20Product%20or%20GNP%20in%20the%20region.%20Irritated%2C%20the%20king%20had%20replied%20that%20it%20was%20more%20important%20that%20people%20were%20happier%20with%20the%20way%20they%20were%20going%2C%20that%20was%20the%20gross%20national%20term%20to%20be%20measured.%20Thus%2C%20GNH%20was%20born.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20frequent%20change%20in%20governing%20parties%20reveals%20the%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20solutions%20so%20far%20offered%2C%20it%20also%20reveals%20a%20deepening%20of%20democracy.%20In%20the%20first%20elections%2C%20only%20two%20parties%20qualified%20for%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20to%20run%20for%20an%20election%20a%20party%20has%20to%20have%20candidate%20from%20all%2020%20of%20its%20dzonkhags%2C%20or%20districts%2C%20of%20the%20country%20and%20all%2047%20National%20Assembly%20constituencies.%20This%20election%20there%20were%20five.%20Unlike%20the%20relatively%20empty%20slogans%20of%20earlier%20elections%2C%20now%20the%20candidates%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Fseeded-candidates-present-dilemma-to-bartsham-shongphu-voters%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edetailed%20pledges%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20providing%20real%20%E2%80%93%20and%20tough%20%E2%80%93%20challenges%20for%20voters%20to%20make%20up%20their%20minds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20A%20journalist%20friend%20of%20mine%2C%20also%20ran%20for%20elections%20this%20year%2C%20and%20although%20her%20party%20did%20not%20make%20it%20past%20the%20first%20round%20%E2%80%93%20the%20second%20round%20has%20a%20face-off%20between%20the%20two%20leading%20parties%20if%20no%20one%20party%20gets%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20vote%20share%20%E2%80%93%20the%20fact%20that%20young%2C%20idealistic%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20their%20life%20savings%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20through%20democratic%20means%20says%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20appeal%20of%20democratic%20politics%20in%20Bhutan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20hard%2C%20these%20days%2C%20to%20be%20enthused%20by%20democracy.%20The%20power%20of%20money%2C%20the%20vanity%20and%20narcissism%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20global%20wars%2C%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20trust%20that%20discussion%20and%20compromise%20can%20lead%20to%20good%20solutions.%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20story%20of%20deepening%20democracy%20becomes%20that%20much%20more%20important%20in%20this%20context.%20Against%20all%20odds%2C%20this%20country%20that%20had%20limited%20experience%20of%20elections%20and%20deliberative%20lawmaking%20except%20at%20the%20highest%20echelons%2C%20has%20embraced%20and%20committed%20itself%20to%20bettering%20itself%20through%20democratic%20means.%20Despite%20its%20many%20problems%2C%20its%20people%20have%20embraced%20a%20pathway%20that%20they%20had%20only%20once%20accepted%20reluctantly.%20Grumbling%2C%20dissatisfied%2C%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20pathway%20to%20progress%20together%2C%20in%20a%20manner%20they%20are%20(somewhat)%20happy%20with.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20can%20be%20no%20greater%20paean%20of%20praise%20to%20democracy%20or%20GNH%20both%2C%20than%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOmair%20Ahmad%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704778358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09104658%2F38483611462_4a890e6997_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbhutan-election-monarchy-happiness%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20the%20severe%20challenges%20that%20Bhutan%20faces%20%E2%80%93%20from%20its%20economy%20to%20its%20security%20%E2%80%93%20its%20stable%20and%20deepening%20democracy%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20bright%20spots%20in%20South%20Asian%20and%20global%20politics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbhutan-election-monarchy-happiness%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Six%20Things%3A%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Convicts%20Being%20Sent%20Back%20to%20Prison%20Is%20a%20Verdict%20on%20Much%20More%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20of%20sending%20the%20convicted%2011%20back%20to%20jail%2C%20the%20resilient%20survivor%20of%20murderous%20attempts%20and%20gang%20rapes%20in%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20violence%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano%20has%20said%20she%20felt%20it%20was%20new%20year%20and%20she%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftoday-i-can-breathe-again-says-bilkis-bano-after-landmark-supreme-court-judgement%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecould%20breathe%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20supreme%20court%20has%20allowed%20many%20to%20reaffirm%20their%20faith%20in%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20%E2%80%9CI%20thank%20the%20honourable%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20for%20giving%20me%2C%20my%20children%20and%20women%20everywhere%2C%20this%20vindication%20and%20hope%20in%20the%20promise%20of%20equal%20justice%20for%20all%E2%80%9D%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20what%20other%20political%20significance%20does%20this%20landmark%20order%20have%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReminder%20of%20where%20this%20government%20stands%20on%202002%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20immediately%20brought%20back%20the%20memories%20of%20the%20other%20heinous%20crimes%20committed%20in%20the%20name%20of%20avenging%20the%20burning%20of%20the%20train%20carrying%20%3Cem%3Ekarsevaks%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20Ayodhya%20in%20the%20Sabarmati%20Express%20in%20Godhra%2C%2022%20years%20ago%20in%20February.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20chief%20minister%20was%20then%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20having%20recently%20taken%20charge.%20The%20deaths%2C%20mayhem%20and%20destruction%20under%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20watch%20put%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20politics%20on%20a%20polarised%20and%20charged%20path.%20On%20April%201%2C%202002%2C%20Justice%20(retired)%20J%20S%20Verma%2C%20then%20chairperson%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20(NHRC)%20noted%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fas-nhrc-head-justice-verma-set-the-stage-for-justice-in-2002-riots%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einvestigations%20in%20these%20cases%20were%20being%20%E2%80%9Cinfluenced%20by%20extraneous%20considerations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20players%20and%20recommended%20CBI%20probe%20into%20five%20cases%2C%20the%20Godhra%20carnage%2C%20killings%20at%20Gulberg%20Society%2C%20Naroda%20Patiya%2C%20Best%20Bakery%20in%20Vadodara%20and%20Sardarpura%20in%20Mehsana.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReinforces%20why%20cases%20were%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20what%20has%20changed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20spoke%20of%20fraudulent%20measures%20adopted%20by%20the%20state%20government%20to%20secure%20the%20May%202022%20order.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20said%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20complicity%20with%20the%20convicts%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20tandem%E2%80%9D%20with%20convict%2C%20breached%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20usurped%20power%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-bilkis-bano-state-of-gujarat-remission-convict-246114%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereports%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Two%20cases%2C%20%3Cem%3EBest%20Bakery%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%3Cem%3E%20Bilkis%20Bano%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20were%20moved%20out%20from%20Gujarat%20to%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Farticleshow%2F6249440.cms%3Futm_source%3Dcontentofinterest%26utm_medium%3Dtext%26utm_campaign%3Dcppst%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20in%202010%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20how%20then%20chief%20minister%20Modi%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Crabble-rousing%20speech%E2%80%9D%20that%20transfer%20of%20the%20case%20outside%20Gujarat%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20be%20an%20insult%20to%20the%20state%20as%20well%20as%20its%20judiciary.%E2%80%9D%20Turns%20out%20that%20the%20supreme%20court%20has%20noted%20in%202024%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20this%20very%20apprehension%20%5Bof%20acting%20in%20tandem%20with%20convicts%5D%20which%20led%20this%20Court%20to%20transfer%20the%20trial%20out%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20to%20Maharashtra.%20In%20matters%20of%20the%20when%20cases%20were%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20which%2C%20through%20hearings%20and%20orders%20over%20the%20years%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fgujarat-2002-cases-moving-key-riot-trials-out-to-indicting-state-what-supreme-court-once-said-and-did-7994865%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecalled%20for%20%E2%80%9Cfair%20and%20impartial%20investigation%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20into%20the%20cases%20of%20violence%20in%202002.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%20verdict%20comment%20on%20BJP%20and%20Union%20government%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20apex%20court%20also%20noted%20that%20if%20the%20convicts%20can%20%E2%80%9Ccircumvent%20the%20consequences%20of%20their%20conviction%2C%20peace%20and%20tranquillity%20in%20the%20society%20will%20be%20reduced%20to%20a%20chimaera.%E2%80%9D%20Gujarat%20has%20the%20same%20chief%20minister%20in%20office%2C%20Bhupendra%20Patel%20in%20May%202022%2C%20as%20it%20does%20now.%20The%20political%20dispensation%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20is%20the%20same.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20home%20ministry%20had%20on%20August%2015%20last%20year%2C%20cleared%20the%20remission.%20The%20union%20government%20okayed%20whatever%20%E2%80%9Ccomplicity%E2%80%9D%20with%20convicts%2C%20the%20supreme%20court%20has%20noted%20in%20its%20order.%20PM%20Modi%2C%20who%20spoke%20of%20crimes%20against%20women%20in%20Congress-run%20Rajasthan%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Minister%20for%20Women%20and%20Child%20Welfare%2C%20the%20BJP%20Mahila%20wing%2C%20senior%20women%20ministers%20and%20Home%20Minister%2C%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20also%20an%20MP%20from%20Ahmedabad%20are%20absolutely%20quiet%20on%20this%20important%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Leaflet%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Erevealed%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Home%20Ministry%20okayed%20the%20remission%20of%20sentence%20to%20the%20guilty%2C%20issuing%20a%20letter%20to%20that%20effect%20on%20July%2011.%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20the%20letter%20of%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20granting%20its%20approval%20to%20the%20premature%20release%20of%2011%20gang%20rape%20convicts%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FBilkisBano%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23BilkisBano%3C%2Fa%3E%20case.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FscYY8fxBza%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FscYY8fxBza%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20The%20Leaflet%20(%40TheLeaflet_in)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTheLeaflet_in%2Fstatus%2F1582037729726332928%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2017%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Nari%20vandan%E2%80%99%20under%20a%20dark%20cloud%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20what%20PM%20Modi%20spoke%20about%20women%20in%20his%20Independence%20Day%20speech%20last%20year.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20spoke%20of%20respecting%20women%2C%20women%20figured%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1948808%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E21%20times%20in%20his%20speech%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20bill%2C%20though%20promising%20reservation%20in%20an%20indefinite%20future%2C%20involved%20talk%20of%20naari%20vandan%20(respecting%2Fpraying%20to%20women).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20said%2C%20while%20introducing%20the%20bill%2C%20%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20God%20has%20given%20me%20the%20opportunity%20to%20take%20this%20forward%E2%80%A6Our%20Government%20is%20bringing%20a%20new%20Bill%20today%20on%20Women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20both%20Houses.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Sanskari%20Brahmin%E2%80%99%20logic%20gets%20a%20reality%20check%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2011%20convicted%20for%20the%20rape%20of%20Bilkis%20Bano%20and%20released%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20are%20%E2%80%9CBrahmins%E2%80%9D%20and%20have%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20sanskaar%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20the%20BJP%20MLA%20from%20Godhra%2C%20CK%20Raulji%20at%20the%20time.%20They%20were%20feted%20with%20sweets%20and%20garlands%20after%20their%20release.%20C.K.%20Raulji%20was%20also%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20the%20two%20BJP%20leaders%20who%20were%20part%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20panel%20that%20unanimously%20decided%20to%20release%20the%20rapists.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20decision%20was%20taken%20after%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20remission%20and%20the%20matter%20was%20passed%20onto%20the%20state%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETook%20four%20gutsy%20women%20to%20push%20for%20justice%2C%20not%20the%20state%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20at%20the%20state%20level%20and%20in%20the%20centre%20was%20one%20with%20the%20convicts%20on%20this%2C%20arguing%20for%20them%2C%20never%20speaking%20up%20for%20the%20survivor.%20It%20took%20women%20petitioners%2C%20expelled%20TMC%20MP%2C%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20ex-CPI(M)%20MP%2C%20Subhasini%20Ali%2C%20social%20worker%2C%20Revati%20Laul%20and%20Rooprekha%20Verma%20to%20petition%20the%20supreme%20court%20and%20move%20on%20Bilkis%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20behalf.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20fact%20that%20it%20took%20independent%20women%20to%20fill%20in%20for%20the%20state%2C%20and%20stand%20up%20for%20the%20cause%20of%20justice%20for%20a%2021-year%20old%20Bilkis%20Bano%20in%202002%2C%20then%20five%20months%20pregnant%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F10%2F18%2Findias-modi-government-approved-release-of-bilkis-banos-rapists%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewho%20survived%20gang%20rapes%2C%20the%20murder%20of%20her%20three-year%20old%20child%20and%20eight%20others%20in%20her%20family%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20well%20as%20her%20unborn%20child%2C%20speaks%20volumes%20about%20the%20state%20of%20justice%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20in%20India%20today.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704777830000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-bano-order-meaning-womens-rights-modi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20order%20draws%20into%20focus%20the%20centre%E2%80%99s%20complicity%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20this%20and%20reminds%20India%20of%20why%20cases%20were%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat.%20BJP%20MLA%E2%80%99s%20'sanskari%20Brahmin'%20remarks%20for%20convicts%20meets%20reality%20and%20shows%20that%20women%20need%20to%20push%20for%20justice%2C%20the%20state%20won%E2%80%99t.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-bano-order-meaning-womens-rights-modi%22%2C%22cdnAmp